==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Commutation ticket
<hw>Com`mu*ta"tion tick"et</hw>. <def>A ticket for transportation at a
reduced rate in consideration of some special circumstance, as increase
of travel; specif., a ticket for a certain number of, or for daily,
trips between neighboring places at a reduced rate, such as are commonly
used by those doing business in a city and living in a suburb.
Commutation tickets are excepted from the prohibition against special
rates contained in the Interstate Commerce Act of Feb. 4, 1887 (<au>24
Stat. 379</au>), and in 145 U. S. 263 it was held that <xex>party
tickets</xex> were also excepted as being ⟦ldquo⟧obviously within the
commuting principle.⟦rdquo⟧</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Commutative</ent>⟦br⟧
